Alhaji Ahmadu Dahiru, Chairman, Transition Administration, Mubi South Local Government of Adamawa, on Saturday said suspected kidnappers had killed two policemen and abducted seven people in the area. Dahiru told the News Agency of Nigeria ( NAN) in Gyela that the incident occurred along Mubi – Gyela road last Tuesday. “Kidnappers terrorise our communities on a daily basis and they kidnap people at will in broad day and night. “They killed two policemen last Tuesday who were on patrol along Mubi – Gyela road. “As I m talking to you, three days ago they abducted five people in Kwaja and two in Sauda village,” Dahiru said. Halt passage of Hate Speech bill, clerics urge National… FUTA NASU kicks against expulsion of Chairman Bayelsa poll: 7 PDP govs, chairman, others storm Yenagoa Sokoto Senator commends FG on closure of land borders ALSO READ:  Pray for Nigeria, our leaders at all times, Olukoya tells Christians He said that the kidnappers were hiding on top of some hills along Nigeria – Cameron border. Dahiru said that the communities had lost millions of naira to kidnappers in ransoms. DSP Sulaiman Nguruje, Spokesman, Adamawa Police Command, confirmed the incident, saying that a team of security operatives were deployed to comb the area. He appealed to the people of the state to report any suspicious and strange character to the nearest security outpost. (NAN) SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
